{
  "texts": [
    "The resolution of the quantum master equations is performed in one dimension.",
    "We have developed a new complex potential, specifically tailored to model the three-dimensional phenomenology [166].",
    "In addition, to obtain tractable equations for the evolution of a Q Q pair, the center of mass degrees of freedom were integrated out.",
    "Model ingredients• In-medium potential One-dimensional temperaturedependent complex potential parameterized [166] to reproduce decay widths and mass spectra of the threedimensional potential by Lafferty and Rothkopf [108].• Vacuum limit of potential/spectroscopy In the vacuum, the real part of the potential is linear with a saturation corresponding to twice the mass of the lightest D or B meson.",
    "The mass spectra of charmonium and bottomonium states are reproduced with a precision of 20 MeV."
  ]
}